# MURU Core Operating Model

- Follow a strict order for non-trivial work: Plan -> Implement -> Verify -> Report.
- Start from existing project patterns before introducing new abstractions.
- Keep changes small, reviewable, and scoped to the user request.
- Prefer immutable updates and pure helper functions where practical.
- If a task affects architecture or many files, propose the plan first and then execute.

## Definition Of Done

- User request implemented end-to-end.
- Relevant checks/tests run and results reported.
- No style or behavior conflicts with MURU brand and product rules.
- Any risks, trade-offs, or deferred work explicitly listed.
